<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-21T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-21T05:00:00-05:00" n="551" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d551">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">352.1121 Fernandez, Antonio/111:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Gibraltar</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Williams</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Gibraltar</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-21T10:00:00+00:00">November 21, 1937—10
                                    a.m.</date><lb/>[Received November 21—7:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Following telegram has been received from Fisher, Palma de Mallorca via
                            British Navy: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“19th Fernandez sentenced 20 years wife 12 years.</p>
                                <p>General state[s] pardon cannot be obtained here. Application for
                                    pardon must be made to Burgos. Please advise.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Williams</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>